written in Python and based on ', '.', 'Main features:', 'WsgiDAV is a stand-alone WebDAV server with SSL support, that can be
installed and run as Python command line script on Linux, OSX, and Windows:', 'Run ', ' for a list of available options.', 'python-pam is needed if using pam-login on Linux or OSX:', ' Windows users may prefer the
', '
(see ', ' section).', 'WebDAV is a superset of HTTP, so WsgiDAV is also a performant, multi-threaded
web server with SSL support.', 'WsgiDAV is also a Python library that implements the WSGI protocol and can
be run behind any WSGI compliant web server.', 'WsgiDAV is implemented as a configurable stack of WSGI middleware
applications.', '
Its open architecture allows to extend the functionality and integrate
WebDAV services into your project.', '
